{
  "text": "Finally, Vanfleteren et al. identified a cluster of subjects with less comorbidity [CITATION_1] . Interestingly, COPD patients without significant rates of major comorbidities were also found in other studies [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Although these data suggest that COPD may occur in the absence of other comorbidities, this absence may be interpreted differently in younger subjects (in whom comorbidities may occur later with ageing, if they survive long enough) and in older subjects (in whom these comorbidities are presumably less likely to occur as they did not in previous years). Nevertheless, at a similar level of FEV 1 , patients with less comorbidities were suggested to have less COPD exacerbations [CITATION_4] .",
  "correct_citation": {
